Gauteng has recorded 209 new COVID-19 related deaths out 312 the country has registered in the last 24 hours. This brings to 6 655 the death toll in the country, which continues to be the epicentre of the virus in Africa. 44 of the new deaths are from the Eastern Cape, 37 from KwaZulu-Natal, 18 from Western Cape and 4 from Northern Cape. South Africa has recorded 12 204 new cases of the novel coronavirus, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 434 200. Gauteng still has the most cases provincially with 156 821 total cases, accounting for 36.1% of the country’s total. The Western Cape has recorded the most deaths provincially, accounting for 2 845 of total deaths. Update on the coronavirus
